Hello.

02:48.711 --> 02:49.645
Renard Perez.

02:49.712 --> 02:50.912
Amy Fleming.

02:50.980 --> 02:53.549
That was absolutely amazing.

02:53.617 --> 02:55.384
I've never seen anything
like it.

02:55.452 --> 02:56.585
What kind of horses
are they?

02:56.653 --> 02:57.818
Andalusians.

02:57.886 --> 03:00.255
Mercutio and Laertes.

03:00.322 --> 03:01.989
They're absolutely
beautiful.

03:02.057 --> 03:03.191
And talented,

03:03.259 --> 03:04.792
but I shouldn't say that
out loud.

03:04.860 --> 03:06.261
They're a couple of divas;

03:06.328 --> 03:08.663
That's what happens
when you put them on a stage.

03:08.730 --> 03:09.750
- For...
- Ah,

03:09.830 --> 03:11.499
"Dark Horse".
It's an equestrian show.

03:11.567 --> 03:12.900
We're getting ready
to open up in Calgary.

03:12.968 --> 03:14.100
I've heard about it.

03:14.169 --> 03:15.135
You're the director,
aren't you?

03:15.203 --> 03:17.504
Director?
That's a bit theatrical.

03:17.572 --> 03:18.772
No,
I'm just a horse trainer.

03:18.839 --> 03:20.106
That's all.

03:20.175 --> 03:21.775
Actually, they train me
more than I train them.

03:21.842 --> 03:23.477
I have a lot to learn,

03:23.545 --> 03:25.145
this is the best place
to do it.

03:25.213 --> 03:26.180
Wow...

03:26.247 --> 03:27.614
So do you come out here
a lot?

03:27.682 --> 03:29.082
I'm gonna be trapped
in the city.

03:29.150 --> 03:31.517
But for now,
I bring my tent out here,

03:31.585 --> 03:33.986
camp with the horses
and we play together.

03:34.054 --> 03:35.988
Just don't
tell them it's a rehearsal

03:36.056 --> 03:37.523
I won't.

03:37.591 --> 03:38.991
Well, I'll...
I'll leave you to it.

03:39.059 --> 03:40.826
No, no...
Take a seat.

03:40.894 --> 03:42.195
Front row.

03:42.262 --> 03:43.896
They love an audience.

03:43.963 --> 03:45.263
Thanks.

